# gsi-cli Presentation Architecture

The CLI UI uses a single layout root in `App.tsx` instead of atomic component layering.

## 1) Layout Ownership

- `App.tsx` owns persistent header + switchable body.
- `AppEffects` is preserved for bootstrap and sync hooks.
- Do not reintroduce `atoms`, `molecules`, or `organisms` folders for gsi-cli.

## 2) State Boundaries

- Redux selectors/thunks remain the source of truth for app/system state.
- Local React state in `App.tsx` controls screen mode and cursor positions.
- Config editing must use a local draft and dispatch save only on explicit confirmation.

## 3) Interaction Model

- Header always shows Steam status, CS2 status, and Gateway status.
- Body mode behavior:
  - Idle gateway: `start`, `config`, `exit`
  - Online gateway: `stop`, `exit`
- Config mode supports up/down field navigation plus save/cancel.

## 4) Implementation Guardrails

- Reuse existing store contracts (`startGateway`, `stopGateway`, `saveCliConfig`, `exitCli`).
- Keep the UI terminal-first and keyboard-driven (`ink` + clear focus state).
